  "buggy_functions": ["azx_init_chip"],
  "confidence": 0.85,
  "reasoning": "The bug is a race condition in azx_init_chip between interrupt initialization and CORB/RIRB initialization. The function currently enables interrupts (azx_int_enable at line 1219) before initializing the codec command I/O (azx_init_cmd_io at line 1223). After a resume from suspend, the hardware controller may generate interrupts immediately after reset, but if the RIRB is not yet initialized, the interrupt handler (azx_interrupt) tries to process responses from an uninitialized RIRB, causing the RIRB read/write pointers to get out of sync. This leads to codec communication failures manifested as timeout errors. The fix is to move azx_init_cmd_io before azx_int_enable to ensure the RIRB is ready before interrupts are enabled. This regression appeared in v3.7.1 likely due to changes in interrupt handling or reset behavior compared to v3.6.11."
}

